    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/805.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to France</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Embassy at Tokyo sends the following telegram [see <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra</hi>, telegram March 18.]</p>
                <p>You will consult the Foreign Office as to the nature of its intended replies to
                    the Russian and Japanese Governments and as to its understanding of the next
                    step to be taken. Repeat the foregoing to the embassies at Berlin and London for
                    similar action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
